---
title: "Sequence: DMRG Sweep Step — Arena Allocation Lifecycle"
---
sequenceDiagram
    participant Engine as DMRGEngine
    participant Arena as SweepArena
    participant Bump as bumpalo::Bump
    participant Tensor as DenseTensor<'a>
    participant Owned as DenseTensor<'static>

    Note over Engine,Owned: One sweep step (repeated per bond)

    Engine->>Arena: alloc_tensor(shape)
    Arena->>Bump: alloc_slice_fill_copy(n, T::zero())
    Bump-->>Arena: &'a [T] (bump-allocated slice)
    Arena->>Tensor: DenseTensor::borrowed(shape, &'a [T])
    Arena-->>Engine: TempTensor<'a> (Borrowed storage)

    Note over Engine: Perform contractions,<br/>SVD on temporary tensors

    Engine->>Tensor: .slice_axis(axis, start, end)
    Tensor-->>Engine: DenseTensor<'a> (offset advanced, same buffer)

    Engine->>Tensor: .as_mat_ref()
    Tensor-->>Engine: MatRef<'a> (zero-copy 2D view)

    Note over Engine: SVD produces final result —<br/>must persist beyond arena reset

    Engine->>Tensor: .into_owned()
    Tensor->>Owned: gather elements → Vec<T>
    Owned-->>Engine: DenseTensor<'static> (heap-owned)

    Note over Engine: All temporaries dropped,<br/>only owned result survives

    Engine->>Arena: reset()
    Arena->>Bump: reset() — O(1) reclaim
    Note over Bump: All bump memory reused<br/>for next sweep step
